<paragraph id="8BF23870F91848EC287430C2FB36F8A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
<bibRefCitation id="FD6F2CB43F71EEEDCDBD09C60BEDCEDA" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris (1983)</bibRefCitation>
reported two varieties of this species from the nearby San Rafael Swell: 
<taxonomicName id="20EAEDA1B2AE9AEB6E68A532A54C2C06" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus desperatus var. desperatus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="desperatus" variety="desperatus">Astragalus desperatus var. desperatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FB0DD61B7A5AA4582E996B091884AF3B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus desperatus var. petrophilus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="desperatus" variety="petrophilus">Astragalus desperatus var. petrophilus</taxonomicName>
M.E. Jones. Both varieties are accepted in 
<bibRefCitation id="6945A5041DE422FD8D8B4F07B09BA5A6" author="Welsh, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University Press, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="North American species of Astragalus Linneaus (Leguminosae): a taxonomic revision" year="2006">Welsh (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="5CA7A6D6A193E651A4D580614E9AA3AB" author="Barneby, RC" journalOrPublisher="New York Botanical Garden, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Atlas of North American Astragalus" year="1964">Barneby (1964)</bibRefCitation>
treats this species as containing var. 
<taxonomicName id="204A509C916EE745208DA7CDFE876775" lsidName="desperatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="species" species="desperatus">desperatus</taxonomicName>
and var. conspectus Barneby, the later of which is synonymous with Welsh's 
<taxonomicName id="564E034FB6F4148C6381B6E0D98440B4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus barnebyi" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barnebyi">Astragalus barnebyi</taxonomicName>
S.L. Welsh &amp; N.D. Atwood (
<bibRefCitation id="F2C5098DD8699A214D1FFD5D67F58E8C" author="Welsh, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University Press, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="North American species of Astragalus Linneaus (Leguminosae): a taxonomic revision" year="2006">Welsh 2006</bibRefCitation>
). As our collection was vegetative, we were unable to identify it to variety.
</paragraph>
